1
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:34,879
I'm not going.

2
00:01:35,760 --> 00:01:36,599
It's between you two.

3
00:01:36,599 --> 00:01:37,920
You can sort it out yourselves.

4
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:39,079
I'm not

5
00:01:39,079 --> 00:01:40,159
being your peacemaker.

6
00:01:41,239 --> 00:01:43,159
You didn't explain yourself clearly.

7
00:01:43,239 --> 00:01:44,319
Go explain it yourself.

8
00:01:44,879 --> 00:01:45,799
Kid,

9
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:46,959
it's time to grow up.

10
00:01:47,719 --> 00:01:48,359
I can't.

11
00:01:48,719 --> 00:01:50,000
And I can't be bothered explaining it to him.

12
00:01:50,239 --> 00:01:51,400
Explaining only makes it look worse.

13
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:53,079
Besides, the rural free clinic...

14
00:01:53,319 --> 00:01:54,799
It doesn't matter whether I go.

15
00:01:54,959 --> 00:01:56,239
You're not going for the clinic.

16
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:58,040
What are you talking about?

17
00:01:58,959 --> 00:02:00,120
Haven't you noticed?

18
00:02:01,719 --> 00:02:02,799
Ouyang Da—

19
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:04,439
she's a pharmaceutical rep.

20
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:05,920
Why is she joining a rural free clinic?

21
00:02:06,159 --> 00:02:06,840
Don't you find that strange?

22
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:09,960
What's strange about it?

23
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:12,439
I think

24
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:14,319
the two of them

25
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:16,000
must have something going on.

26
00:02:17,199 --> 00:02:18,240
No way.

27
00:02:18,759 --> 00:02:20,159
They broke up ages ago.

28
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,840
And now they're vendor and client.

29
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:24,000
That's exactly when things get ambiguous.

30
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:26,039
Working side by side,

31
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,080
cooperating closely,

32
00:02:27,199 --> 00:02:28,520
seeing each other all the time...

33
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:30,719
Next comes rekindled romance.

34
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:34,000
When you put it that way,

35
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,159
it is a little complicated.

36
00:02:36,319 --> 00:02:36,840
But

37
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:38,599
one is a department director,

38
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:39,759
and the other is a pharmaceutical rep.

39
00:02:40,159 --> 00:02:41,000
Don't tell anyone

40
00:02:41,039 --> 00:02:42,439
about their past.

41
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:44,240
If people at the hospital hear,

42
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:45,000
they'll get the wrong idea.

43
00:02:45,319 --> 00:02:45,840
Don't worry.

44
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,360
No one would believe me anyway.

45
00:02:50,759 --> 00:02:51,599
But think about it:

46
00:02:52,919 --> 00:02:53,960
their youthful days,

47
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:55,879
a campus romance...

48
00:02:56,199 --> 00:02:57,199
Maybe they were

49
00:02:57,199 --> 00:02:58,280
each other's first love.

50
00:02:58,639 --> 00:03:01,120
Epic, unforgettable,

51
00:03:02,919 --> 00:03:03,599
impossible to forget.

52
00:03:09,199 --> 00:03:10,319
How unforgettable?

53
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:17,599
You just said it.

54
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:20,960
A campus romance, epic,

55
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:22,520
unforgettable.

56
00:03:23,759 --> 00:03:24,439
So unforgettable.

57
00:03:25,319 --> 00:03:25,879
Did I?

58
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:26,879
Did I say that?

59
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,199
What did I just say?

60
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,479
I don't remember at all.

61
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:30,560
What was it?

62
00:03:32,039 --> 00:03:33,159
Then what do you remember?

63
00:03:37,439 --> 00:03:38,159
I remember

64
00:03:38,879 --> 00:03:41,680
I'm Fang Xiaoran's boyfriend.

65
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:44,599
I'd never forget that.

66
00:03:45,919 --> 00:03:47,280
I really don't remember anything else.

67
00:03:48,439 --> 00:03:48,759
Come on,

68
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:51,080
girlfriend.

69
00:04:22,759 --> 00:04:23,360
Director Zhou.

70
00:04:24,639 --> 00:04:25,439
You came alone?

71
00:04:26,319 --> 00:04:27,480
I went to the company first thing

72
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,560
and picked everything up.

73
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,279
Blood pressure monitors, glucose meters, pulse oximeters—

74
00:04:30,319 --> 00:04:31,199
all brand-new.

75
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:32,439
Give me a hand.

76
00:04:33,199 --> 00:04:34,000
Those three

77
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:34,600
clear cases inside.

78
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:34,959
Sure.

79
00:04:34,959 --> 00:04:35,519
And the black one.

80
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:36,319
Director Zhou.

81
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:38,639
Hello. Hello.

82
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:39,079
Hello, hello.

83
00:04:39,079 --> 00:04:39,480
Hello.

84
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:40,879
I'm Zhao Zhijun

85
00:04:40,959 --> 00:04:42,079
from the town hospital's administrative office.

86
00:04:42,439 --> 00:04:43,040
Director Zhao.

87
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:44,720
This is Factory Director Ma.

88
00:04:45,439 --> 00:04:45,839
Director Ma.

89
00:04:45,879 --> 00:04:46,319
Hello.

90
00:04:46,319 --> 00:04:46,959
Hello, hello.

91
00:04:47,079 --> 00:04:47,439
Director Ma,

92
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:48,680
this is

93
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:49,759
Director Zhou

94
00:04:49,759 --> 00:04:50,839
from Cardiology at Dongli Hospital.

95
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:52,199
Director Zhou.

96
00:04:52,199 --> 00:04:52,600
Hello.

97
00:04:52,839 --> 00:04:53,680
These are

98
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:55,079
the young doctors from Dongli's Heart Center.

99
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:56,639
And this is

100
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:57,319
Manager Ouyang from MyAmpere.

101
00:04:57,519 --> 00:04:58,040
She brought us

102
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:59,120
a brand-new batch of equipment.

103
00:04:59,279 --> 00:04:59,959
Thank you so much.

104
00:05:00,319 --> 00:05:02,000
Welcome, leaders, and thank you for your guidance.

105
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:07,879
No health problems.

106
00:05:07,879 --> 00:05:08,639
None at all.

107
00:05:08,639 --> 00:05:09,199
Everything's fine.

108
00:05:09,199 --> 00:05:09,480
Right.

109
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:11,079
Doctors are here, everyone!

110
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:12,839
This medical team

111
00:05:12,879 --> 00:05:13,920
is incredible.

112
00:05:14,399 --> 00:05:16,399
They came from a major hospital in Dongjiang.

113
00:05:16,439 --> 00:05:16,759
Look.

114
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:18,480
Look at that line.

115
00:05:18,759 --> 00:05:20,040
I heard an expert director

116
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:20,959
personally led the team

117
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:22,560
all the way to our little town.

118
00:05:22,879 --> 00:05:23,519
Zhang Diao'e,

119
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:24,600
go line up.

120
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:25,519
Go on.

121
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,720
I'm here with Tingting.

122
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,639
You're a grown woman.

123
00:05:27,639 --> 00:05:28,759
Why argue with a child?

124
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:29,399
I...

125
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,480
Look, there's a young nurse.

126
00:05:32,319 --> 00:05:32,959
No photos.

127
00:05:33,399 --> 00:05:34,240
I'm livestreaming.

128
00:05:34,759 --> 00:05:35,399
No livestreaming either.

129
00:05:36,079 --> 00:05:36,759
Have you registered?

130
00:05:36,879 --> 00:05:37,240
No.

131
00:05:37,639 --> 00:05:38,439
Register here first.

132
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:40,279
Put it right here.

133
00:05:40,839 --> 00:05:41,879
Don't be scared.

134
00:05:42,519 --> 00:05:43,720
It's okay. No need to be afraid.

135
00:05:43,879 --> 00:05:44,480
No injection.

136
00:05:44,639 --> 00:05:45,759
I'm just going to listen.

137
00:05:46,079 --> 00:05:46,519
It won't hurt.

138
00:05:46,519 --> 00:05:47,560
Just a quick listen.

139
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:48,040
It's okay.

140
00:05:48,639 --> 00:05:49,519
Director, let me try.

141
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,160
Little one, look at me.

142
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:53,079
Put it here. Nice and comfortable.

143
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:53,759
It doesn't hurt at all.

144
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:54,480
See?

145
00:05:55,279 --> 00:05:56,000
Look.

146
00:05:56,319 --> 00:05:57,079
Do you know him?

147
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:58,639
Who's this?

148
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,120
Ultraman.

149
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:00,959
Ultraman.

150
00:06:01,079 --> 00:06:02,000
And who is the person

151
00:06:02,079 --> 00:06:02,639
next to Ultraman?

152
00:06:02,839 --> 00:06:04,519
You.

153
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,000
That's right, me.

154
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,639
Ultraman and I are good friends.

155
00:06:09,079 --> 00:06:10,120
He told me

156
00:06:10,319 --> 00:06:11,560
that any child who cooperates

157
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:12,519
with the examination

158
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:13,720
gets a beautiful sticker

159
00:06:13,759 --> 00:06:14,839
from me.

160
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:15,959
Do you want one?

161
00:06:17,079 --> 00:06:17,600
All right.

162
00:06:18,399 --> 00:06:19,920
We're done. Don't worry, everything's fine.

163
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:21,360
Thank you, doctor.

164
00:06:21,399 --> 00:06:21,839
Let's go.

165
00:06:21,959 --> 00:06:22,240
Thank you.

166
00:06:22,360 --> 00:06:23,480
I'll get you a sticker.

167
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:23,839
Let's go.

168
00:06:23,879 --> 00:06:24,120
Come on.

169
00:06:27,199 --> 00:06:28,279
Tingting, let's go too.

170
00:06:28,279 --> 00:06:28,759
They have stickers.

171
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:30,560
They're free.

172
00:06:30,879 --> 00:06:32,199
There's Elsa. Elsa!

173
00:06:32,319 --> 00:06:33,360
Tingting, go get a sticker too.

174
00:06:33,439 --> 00:06:34,399
They're free.

175
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:35,120
Please wait a moment.

176
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:36,720
I'm waiting for my child.

177
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:37,279
Once she gets her sticker...

178
00:06:37,279 --> 00:06:37,959
Come over here first.

179
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:38,439
Come over.

180
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:38,920
Me? Sit down?

181
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:39,720
Yes, right here.

182
00:06:39,879 --> 00:06:40,519
Tingting,

183
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:41,920
Mommy's talking to the doctor.

184
00:06:42,079 --> 00:06:42,319
Come on.

185
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:43,959
Everyone, hold on.

186
00:06:44,399 --> 00:06:45,879
The doctor wants to talk to me.

187
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:48,399
Clubbing.

188
00:06:50,879 --> 00:06:52,000
Do you usually feel unwell?

189
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:53,519
Not really.

190
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:55,720
Just the occasional headache.

191
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,000
I take a couple of painkillers,

192
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,079
and it goes away in a day or two.

193
00:06:59,839 --> 00:07:00,399
Eighty.

194
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:01,639
Other arm.

195
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,040
Besides the headaches,

196
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,160
any other discomfort?

197
00:07:05,319 --> 00:07:05,959
Do you get tired easily?

198
00:07:06,079 --> 00:07:07,160
Short of breath? Chest tightness?

199
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,439
I don't know why,

200
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,000
but lately

201
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:11,439
even a little work tires me out.

202
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:12,439
I have no strength.

203
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:14,240
My husband keeps calling me lazy.

204
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:16,040
Seventy-eight.

205
00:07:18,439 --> 00:07:18,920
Done?

206
00:07:20,079 --> 00:07:22,160
Have you ever had your heart checked?

207
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:23,600
ECG? Echocardiogram?

208
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,480
I was checked last month.

209
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:26,560
Because of the headaches,

210
00:07:26,639 --> 00:07:27,680
sometimes even painkillers

211
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:28,519
didn't work.

212
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:29,600
I went to the county hospital.

213
00:07:29,639 --> 00:07:30,839
They ordered something called

214
00:07:30,959 --> 00:07:31,600
an echocardiogram.

215
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,279
They said my heart was fine.

216
00:07:34,839 --> 00:07:35,560
Did they run blood tests?

217
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:36,439
Yes.

218
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:37,720
Nothing serious.

219
00:07:39,319 --> 00:07:40,720
Your oxygen level is dangerously low.

220
00:07:40,839 --> 00:07:41,680
This is not minor.

221
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:43,199
Look, your lips are blue.

222
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:44,399
How long has this been going on?

223
00:07:44,639 --> 00:07:46,639
That's just sun exposure.

224
00:07:46,879 --> 00:07:47,800
It's been like that for a long time.

225
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,120
Take off your jacket.

226
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:51,120
Let me listen.

227
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:52,279
How did it get

228
00:07:52,399 --> 00:07:53,399
as black as a pot?

229
00:07:53,399 --> 00:07:54,839
The doctor said it's blue.

230
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,160
All right, stop talking.

231
00:07:56,199 --> 00:07:56,839
Pull it down.

232
00:07:57,879 --> 00:07:58,360
Tell me.

233
00:07:58,480 --> 00:07:59,639
I told you that darkness wasn't normal.

234
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:00,800
Let me listen.

235
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:01,399
Breathe in.

236
00:08:08,959 --> 00:08:09,399
Again.

237
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:13,199
Once more.

238
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,560
Let me listen to your back.

239
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:18,680
Breathe in.

240
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:20,680
Again.

241
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:24,519
All right.

242
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:25,480
Put your jacket back on.

243
00:08:26,199 --> 00:08:26,680
Are we done?

244
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:29,319
What's your name?

245
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:30,519
Zhang Diao'e.

246
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,600
Zhang Diao'e, listen carefully.

247
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:33,399
Your condition is very serious.

248
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:34,720
If it keeps

249
00:08:34,759 --> 00:08:35,559
getting worse,

250
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,360
it could become life-threatening.

251
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:38,000
You need to go to a hospital immediately

252
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:39,120
for tests and treatment.

253
00:08:39,159 --> 00:08:39,679
Do you understand?

254
00:08:41,399 --> 00:08:42,960
Come to Cardiology at Dongli Hospital and ask for me.

255
00:08:45,919 --> 00:08:48,000
What's your name? Zhou... what?

256
00:08:51,159 --> 00:08:51,440
Look.

257
00:08:51,559 --> 00:08:53,240
This is the doctor's name.

258
00:09:00,519 --> 00:09:01,639
I'm Zhou Xiaofeng.

259
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,360
Go to Cardiology at Dongli Hospital.

260
00:09:03,399 --> 00:09:04,720
Show this note to the receiving doctor,

261
00:09:04,759 --> 00:09:05,919
and they'll arrange the tests.

262
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:07,399
So this note works?

263
00:09:08,039 --> 00:09:08,559
It does.

264
00:09:09,159 --> 00:09:10,240
He's the director of Cardiology.

265
00:09:10,519 --> 00:09:11,000
A leader.

266
00:09:12,039 --> 00:09:13,799
You're their boss?

267
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:14,720
Look.

268
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:15,720
A leader.

269
00:09:16,879 --> 00:09:18,039
Then can I take this note

270
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:19,000
to another hospital?

271
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:20,240
Yes.

272
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:20,879
But you should go

273
00:09:20,879 --> 00:09:21,759
to a larger hospital.

274
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,279
So this note

275
00:09:23,279 --> 00:09:24,080
works anywhere, right?

276
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:24,919
That's not the point.

277
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:26,600
Zhang Diao'e,

278
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:28,039
your life may be

279
00:09:28,039 --> 00:09:28,960
in danger right now.

280
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,159
Do you understand?

281
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:31,919
You must go to a hospital immediately

282
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:32,559
for testing and treatment.

283
00:09:34,399 --> 00:09:35,360
Is it really

284
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,879
that serious?

285
00:09:37,639 --> 00:09:38,639
All right. I understand.

286
00:09:38,759 --> 00:09:39,480
Got it, boss.

287
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,120
Thank you.

288
00:09:40,759 --> 00:09:41,960
Tingting, done with your checkup?

289
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:43,200
Everything's fine, right?

290
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:44,559
Look.

291
00:09:44,559 --> 00:09:45,159
Remember to come to Dongli Hospital.

292
00:09:45,159 --> 00:09:45,799
Everyone,

293
00:09:45,919 --> 00:09:47,120
doctors from the big city

294
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:47,879
really are responsible.

295
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:48,600
Mark that down.

296
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:49,600
He looks refined too.

297
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,039
Just a little fierce.

298
00:09:51,039 --> 00:09:52,320
Doctor, check me too.

299
00:09:53,799 --> 00:09:54,799
Where do you usually feel unwell?

300
00:09:55,879 --> 00:09:57,360
The catheter is in the aorta.

301
00:09:57,399 --> 00:09:58,320
Check with ultrasound.

302
00:09:58,559 --> 00:10:00,039
Okay. Ultrasound confirms

303
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:01,080
the catheter has crossed

304
00:10:01,159 --> 00:10:01,720
the aortic valve.

305
00:10:03,159 --> 00:10:03,679
Director Lin,

306
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:04,840
generally,

307
00:10:04,879 --> 00:10:06,279
the angle between the aorta and catheter

308
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:07,120
can't be too wide.

309
00:10:07,399 --> 00:10:08,399
If it's over 45 degrees,

310
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:09,720
we usually can't perform

311
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,080
transapical TAVR.

312
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:12,559
What do you think

313
00:10:12,639 --> 00:10:13,480
