600
00:17:01,879 --> 00:17:02,639
I'll call again.

601
00:17:04,319 --> 00:17:04,880
Does the nearby town hospital

602
00:17:04,880 --> 00:17:05,519
have a CT scanner?

603
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:06,039
Yes.

604
00:17:06,319 --> 00:17:07,160
How long does it take to get there?

605
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:08,400
About ten minutes by car.

606
00:17:08,559 --> 00:17:09,119
This is urgent.

607
00:17:09,519 --> 00:17:10,200
Take my car first.

608
00:17:10,240 --> 00:17:10,559
Let's get

609
00:17:10,559 --> 00:17:11,039
a CT scan.

610
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:12,319
If it's an ischemic stroke,

611
00:17:12,359 --> 00:17:13,559
thrombolysis must begin

612
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:14,440
within 60 minutes.

613
00:17:15,039 --> 00:17:15,480
Director Zhao,

614
00:17:15,960 --> 00:17:16,640
tell 120

615
00:17:16,799 --> 00:17:17,720
to pick her up directly from the town hospital.

616
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:18,119
Okay.

617
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:19,279
Slowly.

618
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:20,319
Okay.

619
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:21,000
All right.

620
00:17:21,079 --> 00:17:21,599
Hello, Xiao Ang.

621
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:23,240
Navigate to the town hospital.

622
00:17:29,119 --> 00:17:29,599
Although the non-contrast

623
00:17:29,640 --> 00:17:30,119
CT scan

624
00:17:30,119 --> 00:17:30,920
doesn't show much yet,

625
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:31,920
look here.

626
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,079
The gray-white matter differentiation

627
00:17:33,079 --> 00:17:33,839
is beginning to blur.

628
00:17:34,279 --> 00:17:34,920
It appears

629
00:17:35,440 --> 00:17:36,640
to be a new ischemic stroke.

630
00:17:37,440 --> 00:17:38,279
There's no intracranial bleeding,

631
00:17:38,519 --> 00:17:39,519
so thrombolysis can begin as soon as possible.

632
00:17:40,319 --> 00:17:41,000
The ambulance is here.

633
00:17:42,480 --> 00:17:43,160
The county hospital has activated

634
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:44,319
the stroke transfer fast track

635
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,240
and dispatched a vehicle with thrombolytics

636
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:45,720
to meet us.

637
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:46,799
We'll rendezvous on the way.

638
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:48,559
Something's wrong.

639
00:17:49,039 --> 00:17:50,079
Her blood pressure is too high.

640
00:17:50,480 --> 00:17:51,319
I already gave antihypertensives.

641
00:17:51,599 --> 00:17:52,720
Why isn't it coming down?

642
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:53,920
The condition is progressing.

643
00:17:55,119 --> 00:17:55,720
Penlight.

644
00:18:07,480 --> 00:18:08,440
Pupils are equal and reactive.

645
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:09,920
But her heart rate is dropping.

646
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:11,759
This isn't a blood pressure problem.

647
00:18:12,359 --> 00:18:13,720
The hypertension may be reflexive.

648
00:18:14,319 --> 00:18:15,960
Brainstem involvement is causing bradycardia.

649
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:16,920
The elevated blood pressure

650
00:18:17,119 --> 00:18:17,799
is the body's attempt

651
00:18:17,799 --> 00:18:18,880
to maintain cerebral perfusion.

652
00:18:19,759 --> 00:18:20,720
We need to stabilize her heart rate first

653
00:18:20,799 --> 00:18:21,640
and preserve cerebral perfusion.

654
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:23,119
Don't let the ischemic area expand.

655
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:24,519
Give isoproterenol.

656
00:18:24,640 --> 00:18:24,960
Okay.

657
00:19:01,599 --> 00:19:02,200
Great.

658
00:19:02,359 --> 00:19:03,119
It's finally coming down.

659
00:19:03,319 --> 00:19:04,240
The isoproterenol is working.

660
00:19:04,839 --> 00:19:05,640
Prepare the thrombolytic.

661
00:19:05,839 --> 00:19:06,160
Okay.

662
00:19:20,519 --> 00:19:21,640
Family members, step out first.

663
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:22,880
My son.

664
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:23,920
My son!

665
00:19:25,599 --> 00:19:26,119
Son!

666
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:27,480
How is the patient now?

667
00:19:27,559 --> 00:19:28,359
Heart rate is currently 35.

668
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:28,960
She's barely conscious.

669
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:30,279
We've given isoproterenol and atropine,

670
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:31,160
but there has been little response.

671
00:19:31,519 --> 00:19:32,160
The ECG shows

672
00:19:32,559 --> 00:19:33,920
complete heart block.

673
00:19:33,920 --> 00:19:34,799
We're preparing

674
00:19:34,799 --> 00:19:35,359
for temporary pacing.

675
00:19:35,359 --> 00:19:35,839
All right.

676
00:19:35,960 --> 00:19:36,440
Quickly.

677
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:37,519
Doctor, how is my grandson?

678
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:38,240
Make way.

679
00:19:38,319 --> 00:19:38,680
Doctor!

680
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:39,640
Family members can't enter.

681
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:40,799
Please wait outside.

682
00:19:40,799 --> 00:19:41,480
Family members, stay outside.

683
00:19:41,519 --> 00:19:42,279
Wait outside.

684
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:43,160
Mask.

685
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:43,680
Open it.

686
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:46,720
Three, two, one. Move.

687
00:19:47,319 --> 00:19:47,880
Where's the family?

688
00:19:48,039 --> 00:19:48,599
At the door.

689
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:49,599
You get ready first.

690
00:19:49,839 --> 00:19:50,160
Okay.

691
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:54,440
Can you hear me?

692
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,119
Can you hear me?

693
00:19:56,319 --> 00:19:57,119
Bed 1 is in ventricular fibrillation.

694
00:19:57,559 --> 00:19:58,559
Prepare for access.

695
00:19:59,200 --> 00:19:59,839
Get ready to defibrillate.

696
00:20:05,480 --> 00:20:06,400
Unsynchronized, 200 joules.

697
00:20:10,160 --> 00:20:11,559
Confirm rhythm. Charge.

698
00:20:11,720 --> 00:20:12,079
Ready.

699
00:20:12,519 --> 00:20:13,119
Charged.

700
00:20:13,279 --> 00:20:13,680
Clear the bed.

701
00:20:16,240 --> 00:20:16,920
Shock.

702
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:18,160
Director Lin,

703
00:20:18,799 --> 00:20:19,559
Bed 6's blood gas results

704
00:20:19,640 --> 00:20:20,160
are back.

705
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:21,359
Lactate is 25.

706
00:20:21,759 --> 00:20:22,799
Base excess is minus 12.

707
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:26,119
Director,

708
00:20:26,319 --> 00:20:27,480
we've been doing compressions for 40 minutes.

709
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:47,759
The pupils are dilated

710
00:20:48,519 --> 00:20:49,200
and nonreactive.

711
00:20:49,240 --> 00:20:50,000
Family members, please make way.

712
00:20:50,559 --> 00:20:50,920
Quickly.

713
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:52,440
ECMO is here.

714
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:53,200
Director Lin.

715
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:53,960
ECMO.

716
00:20:57,240 --> 00:20:57,799
Come with me.

717
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:01,559
Let me take over.

718
00:21:06,279 --> 00:21:07,000
Doctor!

719
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:07,680
How is my son?

720
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:08,880
How is our family member?

721
00:21:09,160 --> 00:21:10,759
Doctor!

722
00:21:11,160 --> 00:21:11,519
Doctor!

723
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:13,160
How is my brother?

724
00:21:15,680 --> 00:21:16,400
Tell us.

725
00:21:17,119 --> 00:21:18,279
We've done everything we could.

726
00:21:18,839 --> 00:21:19,319
Everything?

727
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:21,000
What does that mean?

728
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:23,759
What do you mean?

729
00:21:23,839 --> 00:21:24,240
My...

730
00:21:25,119 --> 00:21:26,039
My father-in-law

731
00:21:26,599 --> 00:21:28,119
just drank too much today.

732
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:29,519
He's drunk.

733
00:21:29,680 --> 00:21:30,799
Can you check him again?

734
00:21:32,799 --> 00:21:34,000
Please check again.

735
00:21:34,279 --> 00:21:34,680
Doctor.

736
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:37,200
Does he usually have coronary artery disease?

737
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:38,279
Yes.

738
00:21:39,319 --> 00:21:40,960
His heart has never been very good.

739
00:21:41,119 --> 00:21:42,119
He has heart disease.

740
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:44,880
Just 0.2 milligrams of aconitine

741
00:21:44,880 --> 00:21:45,599
can be fatal.

742
00:21:47,880 --> 00:21:48,799
He drank too much.

743
00:21:51,559 --> 00:21:52,319
Usually,

744
00:21:53,279 --> 00:21:54,440
he was too reluctant to drink it.

745
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:56,319
He saved it for his grandson's big day.

746
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:57,759
That was when he finally opened it.

747
00:21:58,440 --> 00:21:59,079
I'm sorry for your loss.

748
00:22:00,039 --> 00:22:02,119
My brother!

749
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:02,920
What about my son?

750
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:04,160
My son, Hanxuan?

751
00:22:04,279 --> 00:22:04,680
And...

752
00:22:05,039 --> 00:22:05,599
and his father?

753
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:06,720
They're still being resuscitated.

754
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:08,880
Please, I'm begging you.

755
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:09,759
Save him.

756
00:22:09,839 --> 00:22:10,759
He's only eighteen.

757
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:11,720
We'll do everything we can.

758
00:22:11,720 --> 00:22:12,960
He's not even eighteen yet.

759
00:22:13,039 --> 00:22:13,799
Please.

760
00:22:13,799 --> 00:22:14,759
We'll do our very best.

761
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,000
Please,

762
00:22:16,079 --> 00:22:17,440
save them.

763
00:22:17,839 --> 00:22:19,759
A joyful day

764
00:22:19,799 --> 00:22:21,599
turned into this.

765
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:22,319
We're preparing to start

766
00:22:22,319 --> 00:22:23,119
continuous renal replacement therapy,

767
00:22:23,160 --> 00:22:24,759
but the ventricular electrical storm is very difficult to control.

768
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:25,559
Within ten minutes,

769
00:22:25,599 --> 00:22:26,559
he developed recurrent ventricular fibrillation.

770
00:22:26,680 --> 00:22:27,680
Despite repeated defibrillation

771
00:22:27,759 --> 00:22:28,359
and CPR,

772
00:22:28,519 --> 00:22:29,559
the outlook remains poor.

773
00:22:29,839 --> 00:22:31,160
We'll have to see whether he makes it through the night.

774
00:22:31,759 --> 00:22:32,519
What about his son?

775
00:22:32,680 --> 00:22:33,519
How is the boy?

776
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:34,640
We're implanting

777
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:35,480
a temporary pacemaker.

778
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:36,680
He may have drunk less,

779
00:22:36,759 --> 00:22:37,599
so his condition is relatively stable.

780
00:22:37,799 --> 00:22:39,200
But he is still not out of danger.

781
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,440
I'll monitor him closely.

782
00:22:40,799 --> 00:22:41,960
How are things on your end?

783
00:22:42,279 --> 00:22:43,160
I'm still at the county hospital.

784
00:22:43,480 --> 00:22:44,279
Thankfully, the transfer was timely.

785
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:45,319
They're performing thrombectomy now.

786
00:22:45,799 --> 00:22:47,119
All right. Keep me updated.

787
00:22:47,359 --> 00:22:48,000
Stay in touch.

788
00:22:55,480 --> 00:22:57,079
That woman was incredibly lucky.

789
00:22:57,960 --> 00:22:59,119
What are the odds?

790
00:22:59,440 --> 00:23:00,400
She had a stroke

791
00:23:00,480 --> 00:23:01,599
right when both of you were there.

792
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:02,839
That's what saved her life.

793
00:23:03,359 --> 00:23:03,880
Otherwise,

794
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:05,160
had she missed the golden treatment window,

795
00:23:05,319 --> 00:23:06,079
as you know,

796
00:23:06,359 --> 00:23:08,039
the outcome could have been unpredictable.

797
00:23:08,799 --> 00:23:09,720
The real credit goes to

798
00:23:09,759 --> 00:23:10,559
the integrated stroke network

799
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:12,119
between your county and township facilities.

800
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:13,799
If you hadn't delivered

801
00:23:13,799 --> 00:23:15,000
the thrombolytic in time

802
00:23:15,079 --> 00:23:15,759
and activated

803
00:23:15,799 --> 00:23:16,839
the transfer fast track in advance,

804
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:18,400
we still don't know how it would have ended.

805
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:19,920
For years,

806
00:23:20,039 --> 00:23:22,039
we've been standardizing

807
00:23:22,279 --> 00:23:23,839
first-contact care at the primary level

808
00:23:23,920 --> 00:23:24,799
and transfer pathways to higher-level hospitals.

809
00:23:25,319 --> 00:23:25,720
Yes.

810
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:27,240
Those measures

811
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,279
have truly benefited many patients.

812
00:23:30,240 --> 00:23:32,039
Director Zhou. Manager Ouyang.

813
00:23:32,480 --> 00:23:33,160
Thank you both.

814
00:23:33,839 --> 00:23:34,839
We barely had time to greet you.

815
00:23:34,920 --> 00:23:35,720
It's a pleasure to meet you.

816
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:36,759
Likewise.

817
00:23:37,359 --> 00:23:38,240
If anything comes up with the patient,

818
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:39,039
contact me anytime.

819
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:39,680
Don't worry.

820
00:23:39,880 --> 00:23:40,960
I sincerely hope

821
00:23:41,039 --> 00:23:41,880
we'll have the chance

822
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:43,079
to invite you both back

823
00:23:43,160 --> 00:23:44,200
for proper guidance

824
00:23:44,279 --> 00:23:45,279
on clinical techniques

825
00:23:45,359 --> 00:23:46,400
and product use.

826
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:47,480
Absolutely.

827
00:23:51,559 --> 00:23:51,880
Goodbye.

828
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:52,359
Goodbye.

829
00:23:58,519 --> 00:23:59,920
None of the ride-hailing apps can find a car.

830
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:02,960
There are cars to town,

831
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:04,400
but no departure times are listed.

832
00:24:04,799 --> 00:24:05,400
The one back to the city

833
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:06,319
should arrive soon.

834
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:07,279
You should go first.

835
00:24:07,319 --> 00:24:08,759
I can go to town and retrieve the car myself.

836
00:24:09,759 --> 00:24:10,839
No. I'll stay with you.

837
00:24:11,240 --> 00:24:12,559
I was worried you were anxious to get home.

838
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:14,039
Is everything okay with your child?

839
00:24:15,079 --> 00:24:16,039
My parents are there,

840
00:24:16,359 --> 00:24:17,160
so it's fine.

841
00:24:23,880 --> 00:24:25,759
Let's sit and wait.

842
00:24:26,079 --> 00:24:27,039
We can wait properly.

843
00:24:31,839 --> 00:24:33,440
Tonight was complete chaos.

844
00:24:34,920 --> 00:24:36,039
It felt like a battlefield.

845
00:24:38,519 --> 00:24:40,039
Just like an ER shift.

846
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:43,960
Director Zhou,

847
00:24:44,119 --> 00:24:45,559
you're still as impressive as ever.

848
00:24:46,279 --> 00:24:47,160
You recognized

849
00:24:47,160 --> 00:24:48,119
aconitine poisoning immediately.

850
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:49,079
Otherwise, we couldn't have

851
00:24:49,160 --> 00:24:50,200
treated everyone so quickly.

852
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:53,039
You were the first to realize

853
00:24:53,119 --> 00:24:54,400
the liquor was the source.

854
00:24:54,759 --> 00:24:56,440
That was because of your broad knowledge.

855
00:24:57,079 --> 00:24:58,400
You were the one who recognized

856
00:24:58,440 --> 00:24:59,640
the raw aconite root.

857
00:25:00,599 --> 00:25:01,519
And what about Aunt Ma?

858
00:25:01,880 --> 00:25:02,279
Without

859
00:25:02,279 --> 00:25:03,200
a CT scan,

860
00:25:03,279 --> 00:25:04,519
you accurately judged it was an ischemic stroke,

861
00:25:04,599 --> 00:25:05,359
not a hemorrhage.

862
00:25:05,759 --> 00:25:07,240
If you hadn't lowered her blood pressure

863
00:25:07,240 --> 00:25:08,200
immediately,

864
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:09,359
thrombolysis wouldn't have been possible.

865
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:10,240
You're the impressive one.

866
00:25:10,359 --> 00:25:10,799
No, no.

867
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:11,880
You're more outstanding.

868
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:12,880
You haven't lost your edge.

869
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:14,079
Your clinical skills are solid.

870
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:21,160
This reminds me

871
00:25:21,519 --> 00:25:22,599
of another time

872
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:24,039
when we kept flattering each other.

873
00:25:24,599 --> 00:25:25,880
The signaling pathway

874
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:27,440
related to cardiomyocyte apoptosis

875
00:25:28,039 --> 00:25:29,400
had us both thrilled.

876
00:25:32,960 --> 00:25:33,519
Look.

877
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:35,680
These twenty injected mice,

878
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:37,319
compared with the controls,

879
00:25:37,440 --> 00:25:38,039
all show

880
00:25:38,039 --> 00:25:39,079
significantly improved cardiac function.

881
00:25:39,759 --> 00:25:41,680
That means this signaling pathway

882
00:25:41,799 --> 00:25:43,079
is indeed related

883
00:25:43,119 --> 00:25:44,079
to cardiomyocyte apoptosis.

884
00:25:45,119 --> 00:25:45,880
That's wonderful.

885
00:25:45,920 --> 00:25:46,640
This paper is definitely

886
00:25:46,680 --> 00:25:47,839
getting indexed by SCI.

887
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:50,680
It was all thanks to your help, Senior Zhou.

888
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:52,519
And your courage to keep pushing forward.

889
00:25:52,880 --> 00:25:54,960
Only because you were there to keep me steady.

890
00:25:55,559 --> 00:25:56,920
Not compared with your exceptional insight.

891
00:25:58,680 --> 00:26:00,160
Mostly because Senior Zhou

892
00:26:00,240 --> 00:26:01,200
is so handsome and charming.

893
00:26:02,240 --> 00:26:02,680
Really?

894
00:26:07,359 --> 00:26:08,759
If you hadn't been beside me back then

895
00:26:08,920 --> 00:26:09,559
and given me a push,

896
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:11,720
I could never have done it alone.

897
00:26:13,119 --> 00:26:14,680
I would've been the first to quit.

898
00:26:14,799 --> 00:26:15,799
If you hadn't pulled me along,

899
00:26:15,880 --> 00:26:17,000
I really would have given up.

900
00:26:17,240 --> 00:26:18,200
No way.

901
00:26:18,480 --> 00:26:19,880
You're not someone who gives up easily.

902
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:22,240
Every time, it was your fearlessness

903
00:26:22,319 --> 00:26:23,319
that pulled me forward.

904
00:26:24,079 --> 00:26:25,200
That's because I knew

905
00:26:25,279 --> 00:26:26,359
you'd always be behind me,

906
00:26:26,359 --> 00:26:27,440
ready to catch me.

907
00:26:27,799 --> 00:26:29,359
Whether then or now,

908
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:31,039
you always make me feel safe.

909
00:26:31,519 --> 00:26:32,519
That's why I say

910
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:34,400
we were made to be

911
00:26:34,720 --> 00:26:35,480
the perfect partners.

912
00:26:41,039 --> 00:26:42,480
Times have changed.

913
00:26:51,759 --> 00:26:52,359
Are you hungry?

914
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:00,319
Two bowls of beef soup, please.

915
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:00,920
Coming right up.

916
00:27:01,519 --> 00:27:02,119
Here you go.

917
00:27:02,200 --> 00:27:02,559
It's hot.

918
00:27:02,759 --> 00:27:03,200
Thank you.

919
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:03,759
Careful.

920
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:04,440
Here.

921
00:27:04,920 --> 00:27:05,839
Thanks.

922
00:27:15,279 --> 00:27:15,799
So warm.

923
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:22,519
Actually,

924
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:24,960
there's something I've never understood.

925
00:27:25,759 --> 00:27:26,200
What?

926
00:27:28,039 --> 00:27:28,799
Back then,

927
00:27:28,839 --> 00:27:30,000
we were so close.

928
00:27:30,359 --> 00:27:32,119
You always gave way to me

929
00:27:32,319 --> 00:27:33,400
and went along with everything I wanted.

930
00:27:33,759 --> 00:27:35,359
Why was that one thing

931
00:27:37,119 --> 00:27:38,640
the exception?

932
00:27:39,640 --> 00:27:41,240
Why did you get so angry

933
00:27:41,480 --> 00:27:42,359
when I went to Professor Fang

934
00:27:45,319 --> 00:27:46,720
that we broke up?

935
00:27:47,160 --> 00:27:48,400
You were the one who broke up with me.

936
00:27:48,759 --> 00:27:49,119
You stopped speaking to me first.

937
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:50,799
Yes,

938
00:27:51,079 --> 00:27:52,079
because what you did crossed a line.

939
00:27:52,839 --> 00:27:54,200
I crossed a line?

940
00:27:55,440 --> 00:27:56,319
I was trying to help you.

941
00:27:56,319 --> 00:27:57,079
I hadn't told anyone

942
00:27:57,400 --> 00:27:58,599
about my mother.

943
00:27:58,920 --> 00:28:00,039
I only told you.

944
00:28:00,079 --> 00:28:00,559
Exactly.

945
00:28:00,599 --> 00:28:01,240
That was why I knew

946
00:28:01,279 --> 00:28:02,119
I was the only person

947
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:03,400
who could help you.

948
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:04,920
I never asked you to help.

949
00:28:04,920 --> 00:28:06,240
But I was your girlfriend.

950
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:21,759
If I didn't help, who would?

951
00:28:22,119 --> 00:28:22,960
I'm not trying to reopen old wounds.

952
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:24,519
I truly

953
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:29,599
never understood.

954
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:30,559
Because back then,

955
00:28:31,559 --> 00:28:32,319
I kept waiting for you.

956
00:28:32,319 --> 00:28:33,200
I thought

957
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:35,319
we'd be like before:

958
00:28:35,559 --> 00:28:36,640
you'd come back, apologize,

959
00:28:38,400 --> 00:28:39,559
and we'd make up.

960
00:28:42,039 --> 00:28:43,079
But you never came.

961
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:44,160
I really didn't expect

962
00:28:46,680 --> 00:28:47,319
you to be so cold.

963
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:48,960
Back then,

964
00:28:49,039 --> 00:28:49,799
I was so afraid of missing your call

965
00:28:49,839 --> 00:28:50,880
that I even took my phone

966
00:28:55,559 --> 00:28:58,119
into the shower.

967
00:28:58,720 --> 00:28:59,880
So I genuinely never understood.

968
00:29:01,440 --> 00:29:02,640
I want to ask you too:

969
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:03,519
did you never think of winning me back?

970
00:29:05,759 --> 00:29:06,279
No.

971
00:29:14,240 --> 00:29:14,720
Yes.

972
00:29:15,359 --> 00:29:15,920
Wait, you...

973
00:29:20,920 --> 00:29:21,799
You know

974
00:29:23,240 --> 00:29:24,160
how I was then.

975
00:29:24,839 --> 00:29:25,640
I had a deep fixation

976
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:26,720
on my mother.

977
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:28,920
I was desperate

978
00:29:28,960 --> 00:29:30,119
to prove myself

979
00:29:30,599 --> 00:29:32,279
and make her regret abandoning me.

980
00:29:34,039 --> 00:29:35,480
But at that moment,

981
00:29:36,039 --> 00:29:37,720
you went to her for help without telling me.

982
00:29:38,160 --> 00:29:38,799
That's why

983
00:29:38,799 --> 00:29:39,759
I reacted so strongly.

984
00:29:42,960 --> 00:29:43,400
Ouyang,

985
00:29:44,640 --> 00:29:45,240
maybe you thought

986
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:46,319
I didn't care that much.

987
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:48,160
But that wasn't true.

988
00:29:48,920 --> 00:29:50,240
It was because I cared so much

989
00:29:51,599 --> 00:29:53,279
that when you ended things,

990
00:29:53,880 --> 00:29:54,960
I felt

991
00:29:55,599 --> 00:29:56,359
once again abandoned

992
00:29:56,519 --> 00:29:57,640
by someone

993
00:29:57,640 --> 00:29:58,319
very important to me.

994
00:30:02,440 --> 00:30:03,400
It wasn't that I didn't want you back.

995
00:30:04,519 --> 00:30:05,079
I was afraid.

996
00:30:10,799 --> 00:30:11,519
Actually, I knew

997
00:30:11,519 --> 00:30:12,359
you were waiting for me.

998
00:30:16,279 --> 00:30:17,640
But seeing you suffer because of me

999
00:30:20,400 --> 00:30:21,319
seemed to give me

1000
00:30:21,319 --> 00:30:22,440
a tiny bit of comfort.

1001
00:30:27,759 --> 00:30:29,119
I was twisted up inside back then.

1002
00:30:34,240 --> 00:30:35,720
Thank you for being honest,

1003
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:38,880
Senior Zhou.

1004
00:30:42,640 --> 00:30:43,200
I'm sorry.

1005
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:45,519
It really was my fault.

1006
00:30:45,839 --> 00:30:46,440
No, no.

1007
00:30:47,960 --> 00:30:49,200
I'm just so glad

1008
00:30:49,519 --> 00:30:50,799
I finally heard the answer today.

1009
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:08,799
What if I had tried to win you back?

1010
00:31:29,359 --> 00:31:29,839
Mom.

1011
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:31,759
What time are you coming home?

1012
00:31:33,319 --> 00:31:33,960
Senlin,

1013
00:31:34,559 --> 00:31:35,799
go to sleep with Grandma first.

1014
00:31:35,839 --> 00:31:37,240
Mom will be home later.

1015
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:38,440
Good night.

1016
00:31:40,839 --> 00:31:41,519
Senlin.

1017
00:31:46,640 --> 00:31:47,480
No matter what,

1018
00:31:49,279 --> 00:31:50,359
I never expected fate

1019
00:31:50,359 --> 00:31:51,039
to bring us together again.

1020
00:31:54,039 --> 00:31:54,599
Neither did I.

1021
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:56,200
I also never expected

1022
00:31:56,759 --> 00:31:57,680
that today,

1023
00:31:57,880 --> 00:31:58,880
I'd hear

1024
00:31:59,599 --> 00:32:00,880
an answer from the past.

1025
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:05,720
Then from now on,

1026
00:32:05,880 --> 00:32:07,000
let's keep working together.

1027
00:32:07,799 --> 00:32:08,279
Right?

1028
00:32:10,839 --> 00:32:11,640
Looking forward to it.

1029
00:32:13,440 --> 00:32:14,319
Take care of me.

1030
00:33:26,559 --> 00:33:27,079
All done.

1031
00:33:28,480 --> 00:33:29,920
The pacemaker is implanted under your skin.

1032
00:33:30,319 --> 00:33:31,839
It will barely affect your daily life.

1033
00:33:32,119 --> 00:33:33,039
Just make sure the wound

1034
00:33:33,039 --> 00:33:33,559
doesn't get infected.

1035
00:33:36,400 --> 00:33:38,559
Iron Boy conversion complete.

1036
00:33:39,559 --> 00:33:41,039
I'm electrically charged now.

1037
00:33:41,240 --> 00:33:42,119
You'd better be careful.

1038
00:33:45,720 --> 00:33:46,480
Stay put in the ICU

1039
00:33:46,480 --> 00:33:47,079
tonight

1040
00:33:47,079 --> 00:33:47,759
for observation.

1041
00:33:48,200 --> 00:33:48,920
If everything is fine tomorrow,

1042
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:49,799
you'll transfer to the regular ward.

1043
00:33:55,720 --> 00:33:56,599
Ma Hanxuan's condition

1044
00:33:56,640 --> 00:33:57,519
is basically stable.

1045
00:33:57,839 --> 00:33:59,359
His father is in Bed 13 up ahead.

1046
00:34:00,119 --> 00:34:01,519
I wanted to place

1047
00:34:01,559 --> 00:34:02,480
the two of them together,

1048
00:34:02,680 --> 00:34:04,000
but his father refused.

1049
00:34:05,160 --> 00:34:06,920
He's currently undergoing hemoperfusion

1050
00:34:06,920 --> 00:34:07,839
to adsorb the toxins.

1051
00:34:08,320 --> 00:34:09,880
Fortunately, he's much better today.

1052
00:34:10,159 --> 00:34:10,840
He's in his prime,

1053
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:12,000
so he had a good baseline condition.

1054
00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:13,679
It's just that his monitor

1055
00:34:13,719 --> 00:34:15,079
still alarms from time to time.

1056
00:34:15,559 --> 00:34:17,360
I'm wondering if it's psychological.

1057
00:34:18,920 --> 00:34:19,880
He was the one who bought

1058
00:34:19,880 --> 00:34:20,719
the raw aconite for the liquor.

1059
00:34:21,119 --> 00:34:22,199
It was meant as a gift for his father,

1060
00:34:22,199 --> 00:34:23,199
but it turned into this.

1061
00:34:23,920 --> 00:34:24,679
No wonder.

1062
00:34:24,719 --> 00:34:26,000
He has little will to live.

1063
00:34:26,559 --> 00:34:28,000
His wife brought him fish soup,

1064
00:34:28,039 --> 00:34:28,800
but he hasn't touched it.

1065
00:34:29,440 --> 00:34:30,320
He won't eat or drink.

1066
00:34:30,400 --> 00:34:31,360
Nothing we say works.

1067
00:34:32,320 --> 00:34:33,920
This can't continue.

1068
00:34:36,039 --> 00:34:37,480
I'll think of another way later.

1069
00:34:51,039 --> 00:34:51,519
Director Lin.

1070
00:34:51,559 --> 00:34:52,000
Hello, Director Lin.

1071
00:34:52,039 --> 00:34:52,840
Director Zhou. Hello.

1072
00:34:55,679 --> 00:34:56,480
Maybe don't drink anything iced.

1073
00:34:56,880 --> 00:34:58,159
Have this. It's gentler

1074
00:34:58,320 --> 00:34:59,119
on the stomach.

1075
00:35:00,679 --> 00:35:01,360
Why?

1076
00:35:03,519 --> 00:35:04,880
Didn't you say your stomach hurt?

1077
00:35:09,400 --> 00:35:12,159
Right. My stomach hurt.

1078
00:35:20,639 --> 00:35:22,079
It didn't.

1079
00:35:24,239 --> 00:35:25,119
I lied.

1080
00:35:26,840 --> 00:35:27,880
That day, I went to Fushan Hospital

1081
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:28,519
for

1082
00:35:28,519 --> 00:35:28,920
a TAVR

1083
00:35:28,920 --> 00:35:29,400
training course.

1084
00:35:29,840 --> 00:35:31,079
You attended a course. So what?

1085
00:35:31,760 --> 00:35:32,880
Why couldn't you tell me?

1086
00:35:33,239 --> 00:35:34,440
I was afraid.

1087
00:35:35,559 --> 00:35:36,599
I'd promised to join

1088
00:35:37,159 --> 00:35:38,679
the rural free clinic, then didn't go.

1089
00:35:39,159 --> 00:35:40,159
I thought you'd be upset.

1090
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:41,440
And besides,

1091
00:35:41,599 --> 00:35:42,320
at our hospital,

1092
00:35:42,320 --> 00:35:43,079
TAVR

1093
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:44,599
is handled by Cardiology.

1094
00:35:44,679 --> 00:35:45,920
If I attended the course,

1095
00:35:47,920 --> 00:35:49,239
I worried you'd have opinions about it.

1096
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:52,679
Do you really think

1097
00:35:52,679 --> 00:35:53,440
I'm that

1098
00:35:53,440 --> 00:35:54,480
small-minded?

1099
00:35:54,880 --> 00:35:56,280
You're not narrow-minded,

1100
00:35:56,360 --> 00:35:57,159
but your heart

1101
00:35:58,400 --> 00:35:59,119
isn't that big either.

1102
00:36:01,119 --> 00:36:02,280
So many cardiac surgeons perform

1103
00:36:02,280 --> 00:36:02,960
TAVR now.

1104
00:36:03,199 --> 00:36:03,960
That's the trend.

1105
00:36:03,960 --> 00:36:05,239
Could I stop it even if I wanted to?

1106
00:36:05,559 --> 00:36:06,960
And if you're the one doing it,

1107
00:36:07,559 --> 00:36:08,760
why would I be unhappy?

1108
00:36:09,559 --> 00:36:10,440
So you're not angry.

1109
00:36:11,159 --> 00:36:12,039
Then we're done with this.

1110
00:36:14,039 --> 00:36:15,360
In that case, I'm having the iced one.

1111
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:22,840
But

1112
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:25,199
Director Sheng arranged the course, didn't he?

1113
00:36:25,760 --> 00:36:26,320
How did you know?

1114
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:28,440
At his previous hospital,

1115
00:36:28,719 --> 00:36:29,760
he also tried hard to promote

1116
00:36:29,760 --> 00:36:30,599
transcatheter valve interventions,

1117
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:32,440
but lacked the right talent.

1118
00:36:33,679 --> 00:36:34,840
Now that he's at Dongli,

1119
00:36:35,840 --> 00:36:36,880
the talent has appeared.

1120
00:36:39,159 --> 00:36:39,800
Me?

1121
00:36:40,719 --> 00:36:41,679
Stop joking.

1122
00:36:42,239 --> 00:36:42,840
TAVR

1123
00:36:42,840 --> 00:36:44,199
just made me curious.

1124
00:36:44,280 --> 00:36:46,159
I wanted to learn a little.

1125
00:36:46,360 --> 00:36:48,000
Surgery is still my main focus.

1126
00:36:49,639 --> 00:36:50,960
Guess who I saw that day.

1127
00:36:51,119 --> 00:36:52,760
Director Luo Qi.

1128
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:53,440
Do you know him?

1129
00:36:53,840 --> 00:36:55,039
He's from my mentor's generation,

1130
00:36:55,280 --> 00:36:56,159
a giant in the field.

1131
00:36:56,559 --> 00:36:57,480
I watched him perform

1132
00:36:57,519 --> 00:36:58,000
a TAVR.

1133
00:36:58,159 --> 00:36:58,880
And guess what?

1134
00:37:01,719 --> 00:37:02,639
It wasn't as good as yours.

1135
00:37:06,760 --> 00:37:07,599
Anyway, from now on,

1136
00:37:07,639 --> 00:37:08,639
do whatever you want.

1137
00:37:09,079 --> 00:37:09,719
If we both perform TAVR,

1138
00:37:09,719 --> 00:37:10,760
we'll compete fairly.

1139
00:37:10,840 --> 00:37:11,639
Let's see who does it better.

1140
00:37:13,519 --> 00:37:15,119
How could I beat you?

1141
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:16,280
You're the professional.

1142
00:37:16,519 --> 00:37:17,599
I'm only an amateur.

1143
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:20,079
Whatever happens,

1144
00:37:20,719 --> 00:37:22,000
no matter what nonsense you come up with,

1145
00:37:22,960 --> 00:37:24,280
don't joke about your health again.

1146
00:37:25,320 --> 00:37:26,599
All right. I know.

1147
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:28,599
I'm going to check on Xiaorui.

1148
00:37:31,199 --> 00:37:31,840
Drink this.

1149
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:32,639
It's gentler.

1150
00:37:51,639 --> 00:37:52,239
Sister Beibei,

1151
00:37:52,719 --> 00:37:53,599
can I sit by the bed

1152
00:37:53,639 --> 00:37:54,000
for a while?

1153
00:37:55,119 --> 00:37:55,880
Only for a moment.

1154
00:37:55,960 --> 00:37:56,639
Don't move around.

1155
00:37:57,159 --> 00:37:58,039
And don't raise your left arm.

1156
00:37:58,159 --> 00:37:58,639
Understand?

1157
00:37:58,800 --> 00:37:59,880
I'm watching you.

1158
00:38:01,079 --> 00:38:01,440
Sit down.

1159
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:03,159
Sister Beibei is beautiful and kind.

1160
00:38:03,679 --> 00:38:04,639
You sure know how to flatter people.

1161
00:38:20,320 --> 00:38:20,880
Sir,

1162
00:38:27,119 --> 00:38:28,079
how old are you?

1163
00:38:33,920 --> 00:38:34,800
Looking at you,

1164
00:38:35,559 --> 00:38:36,679
you're probably a few years younger than my dad.

1165
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:40,199
My father was

1166
00:38:41,519 --> 00:38:42,280
forty-five when he died.

1167
00:38:47,119 --> 00:38:49,719
He was tall and thin,

1168
00:38:51,000 --> 00:38:52,039
not strong like you.

1169
00:38:53,719 --> 00:38:54,840
But seeing you

1170
00:38:56,519 --> 00:38:57,519
makes me think of him again.

1171
00:39:00,159 --> 00:39:01,280
My father once said,

1172
00:39:02,760 --> 00:39:03,800
while your parents are alive,

1173
00:39:04,599 --> 00:39:05,800
there's a curtain

1174
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:07,000
between you and death.

1175
00:39:08,559 --> 00:39:09,719
Once your parents are gone,

1176
00:39:11,039 --> 00:39:12,480
you face death directly.

1177
00:39:15,480 --> 00:39:16,639
After my father died,

1178
00:39:17,559 --> 00:39:18,400
I felt

1179
00:39:19,199 --> 00:39:20,599
I became that curtain.

1180
00:39:21,679 --> 00:39:22,599
As long as I'm alive,

1181
00:39:23,360 --> 00:39:24,679
I can stand between

1182
00:39:25,400 --> 00:39:26,320
my loved ones and death.

1183
00:39:31,119 --> 00:39:31,679
Director Lin.

1184
00:39:35,280 --> 00:39:36,239
Who sits up

1185
00:39:36,239 --> 00:39:37,280
in the comprehensive ICU?

1186
00:39:40,519 --> 00:39:41,079
Lie down.

1187
00:39:41,760 --> 00:39:42,599
Slowly.

1188
00:39:56,000 --> 00:39:56,719
Sister Beibei.

1189
00:39:58,679 --> 00:39:59,199
Sister Beibei.

1190
00:39:59,559 --> 00:40:01,039
Where did the fish soup

1191
00:40:01,039 --> 00:40:02,079
and steamed egg from Bed 13's family go?

1192
00:40:02,239 --> 00:40:02,960
Bed 13 is finally

1193
00:40:02,960 --> 00:40:03,679
willing to eat.

1194
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:04,920
That's great. I'll take it.

1195
00:40:16,599 --> 00:40:17,559
Thank you, Directors.

1196
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:18,920
With both of you

1197
00:40:18,920 --> 00:40:19,599
consulting on my father,

1198
00:40:19,960 --> 00:40:21,880
it's like having double insurance.

1199
00:40:22,039 --> 00:40:22,679
You're welcome.

1200
00:40:22,880 --> 00:40:23,519
Take your medicine on schedule.

1201
00:40:23,679 --> 00:40:23,960
Thank you.

1202
00:40:23,960 --> 00:40:24,440
And come back for follow-up on time.

1203
00:40:24,679 --> 00:40:25,079
We will.

1204
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:26,280
Take care.

1205
00:40:30,119 --> 00:40:31,800
That's the last patient today.

1206
00:40:33,440 --> 00:40:34,639
Ye did well today.

1207
00:40:38,079 --> 00:40:39,239
Ye really did well.

1208
00:40:43,079 --> 00:40:44,079
Director Zhou can treat you to dinner.

1209
00:40:46,760 --> 00:40:47,239
Director,

1210
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:48,559
what about me?

1211
00:40:50,039 --> 00:40:51,159
Can't you feed yourself?

1212
00:40:54,239 --> 00:40:55,360
Handsome young man.

1213
00:40:55,480 --> 00:40:56,280
Pretty doctor.

1214
00:40:56,400 --> 00:40:57,000
Hello, leaders.

1215
00:40:57,079 --> 00:40:57,880
I found the right place.

1216
00:40:57,960 --> 00:40:58,800
You made it.

1217
00:40:59,039 --> 00:41:00,159
Director Zhou asked

1218
00:41:00,159 --> 00:41:01,079
about Director Zhao yesterday.

1219
00:41:01,199 --> 00:41:01,639
Right?

1220
00:41:01,800 --> 00:41:02,920
Director Zhao told me,

1221
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:04,480
so I came today.

1222
00:41:05,559 --> 00:41:07,159
This one's also a leader, right?

1223
00:41:07,199 --> 00:41:08,599
This is Director Lin from Cardiac Surgery.

1224
00:41:08,960 --> 00:41:09,960
Director Lin.

1225
00:41:10,079 --> 00:41:11,400
Hello, Leader Lin.

1226
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:12,119
Please don't call me that.

1227
00:41:12,239 --> 00:41:13,159
There's only one leader here.

1228
00:41:13,880 --> 00:41:14,559
Have a seat.

1229
00:41:15,320 --> 00:41:16,280
What tests have you done?

1230
00:41:16,599 --> 00:41:17,599
The county hospital

1231
00:41:17,639 --> 00:41:19,239
had me do a whole pile of tests.

1232
00:41:19,480 --> 00:41:20,159
Here are the reports.

1233
00:41:20,840 --> 00:41:22,599
They said I had some kind of...

1234
00:41:22,639 --> 00:41:23,320
some kind of fistula.

1235
00:41:23,639 --> 00:41:24,880
They couldn't handle it.

1236
00:41:26,039 --> 00:41:26,920
So I showed them

1237
00:41:26,960 --> 00:41:28,079
the note you gave me.

1238
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:29,639
The nurse at the entrance saw it

1239
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:31,199
and told me to come find you.

1240
00:41:31,920 --> 00:41:33,360
This note really works.

1241
00:41:33,360 --> 00:41:34,119
It is pulmonary arteriovenous malformation.

1242
00:41:34,199 --> 00:41:35,480
Keep that note safe.

1243
00:41:36,880 --> 00:41:37,719
A pulmonary arteriovenous fistula.

1244
00:41:38,280 --> 00:41:39,519
A fistula? Is something leaking?

1245
00:41:39,639 --> 00:41:40,440
Where is it leaking?

1246
00:41:44,440 --> 00:41:45,639
Who wants to explain?

1247
00:41:45,679 --> 00:41:46,920
What is a pulmonary arteriovenous fistula?

1248
00:41:47,639 --> 00:41:48,400
A pulmonary arteriovenous fistula,

1249
00:41:48,519 --> 00:41:49,880
or pulmonary arteriovenous malformation, is very rare.

1250
00:41:49,960 --> 00:41:50,880
It is usually congenital.

1251
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:51,920
It refers to

1252
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:52,800
an abnormal connection

1253
00:41:52,800 --> 00:41:53,519
between the pulmonary artery and pulmonary vein.

1254
00:41:53,719 --> 00:41:55,039
In other words, blood from the pulmonary artery

1255
00:41:55,119 --> 00:41:56,079
bypasses the alveoli

1256
00:41:56,079 --> 00:41:57,119
and flows directly into the pulmonary vein.

1257
00:41:57,280 --> 00:41:59,039
That's why it's also called a pulmonary arteriovenous malformation.

1258
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:01,199
Malformation?

1259
00:42:01,559 --> 00:42:02,760
I'm malformed?

1260
00:42:04,559 --> 00:42:05,639
The patient didn't understand.

1261
00:42:06,360 --> 00:42:07,159
Put simply,

1262
00:42:07,199 --> 00:42:08,280
normally, the blood vessels in your lungs

1263
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:10,079
carry low-oxygen venous blood

1264
00:42:10,159 --> 00:42:10,800
to the lungs

1265
00:42:10,880 --> 00:42:11,840
to pick up oxygen,

1266
00:42:12,079 --> 00:42:13,000
then send it back to the heart.

1267
00:42:13,239 --> 00:42:14,280
But in your case,

1268
00:42:14,320 --> 00:42:15,280
there's an extra shortcut.

1269
00:42:15,440 --> 00:42:16,119
Your blood

1270
00:42:16,119 --> 00:42:17,199
returns directly to the heart

1271
00:42:17,280 --> 00:42:18,960
before it is oxygenated.

1272
00:42:19,360 --> 00:42:20,079
That's why you're hypoxic,

1273
00:42:20,079 --> 00:42:21,079
and your heart is under strain.

1274
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:22,079
Your lips

1275
00:42:22,239 --> 00:42:22,880
and your fingers

1276
00:42:23,079 --> 00:42:24,079
all show signs of low oxygen.

1277
00:42:25,239 --> 00:42:26,119
So that's what it is.

1278
00:42:29,480 --> 00:42:31,239
So this really isn't

1279
00:42:31,280 --> 00:42:32,039
from the sun.

1280
00:42:33,480 --> 00:42:34,280
Is it serious?

1281
00:42:35,159 --> 00:42:35,719
What complications

1282
00:42:35,760 --> 00:42:36,480
can pulmonary arteriovenous fistulas cause?

1283
00:42:36,960 --> 00:42:37,920
Patients may develop

1284
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:39,639
shortness of breath, cyanosis, clubbing,

1285
00:42:39,760 --> 00:42:41,280
headaches, and other symptoms of hypoxemia

1286
00:42:41,320 --> 00:42:42,440
and neurological problems.

1287
00:42:42,679 --> 00:42:44,159
Serious complications also include

1288
00:42:44,239 --> 00:42:45,360
cerebral infarction, brain abscess,

1289
00:42:45,440 --> 00:42:46,519
hemoptysis, and hemothorax.

1290
00:42:49,159 --> 00:42:50,280
That sounds terrifying.

1291
00:42:50,639 --> 00:42:51,320
Don't worry too much.

1292
00:42:51,559 --> 00:42:52,159
Now that you're here,

1293
00:42:52,159 --> 00:42:53,079
we'll take good care of you.

1294
00:42:54,679 --> 00:42:56,039
Leader Lin, what I meant was—

1295
00:42:56,199 --> 00:42:57,440
you're terrifying.
